                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.38/28.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">Davis</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-05T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 5, 1915—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your September 4, 10 a.m. If attainment vote of desired resolution would cause
                    further delay and if you are satisfied that any treaty signed by the President
                    with approval of Cabinet will be promptly ratified without any amendments
                    whatsoever, before the 12th instant, it would not seem necessary to insist on a
                    previous resolution by Chamber of Deputies.</p>
                <p>Referring to last paragraph of your telegram under reference, the Department now
                    confidently expects immediate conclusion of treaty and looks for early favorable
                    action by Chamber.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
